review.reviewBody: As always, brioche was absolutely delightful. Really generous portions and amazing flavor!

We've ordered the Sicilian Meatloaf with pizza toppings meatloaf and Smoked Salmon Pasta in Rose sauce for a couple years. Still delicious but  the portions have been cut dramatically. I will still order these two dishes but I think mgmt should change it back to the usual portion sizes. Thank you
all delicious but fruit salads not fresh, fruit salads are a bit old and melon is fermented a bit

it was a mess! The quiche didn't look like a slice. It was just dumped into the container sideways with a soggy bottom crust and the back crust burnt on the edges. The side of fruit I ordered was not included. So disappointing.

Brioche is a Gastown mainstay for good reason: their flavors are EXCELLENT. But if your ordering delivery be warned, its not as good as in store by a long shot. Its entirely because they load up the container as if its being served in restaurant, so by the time it arrives, anything that was supposed have any texture or crunch is a soggy mess. 

Our French Toast was a syrup-soaked mush; the Bennie was the same, except the culprit in this case was the Hollandaise. 

This could be avoided if they bothered to pack liquid or sauce elements  separately. 

On the plus side, the Ravioli was excellent. I will try again, with the request to pack syrups and sauces separately. I'd advise others to do the same.
